# Splunk Troubleshooting: False Process Down Alert Due to PID File Path Issue

##  Problem
An alert in Splunk indicated that a monitored process had stopped.

However, manual verification showed that the process was running normally.

## Investigation
- Checked process status on server → running
- Reviewed monitoring script → uses PID file to validate process
- Verified PID file → present
- Script unable to read PID file

## Root Cause
An extra space in the file path in the configuration file.

This caused the script to fail in locating the PID file and incorrectly mark the process as stopped.

## ✅ Solution
Corrected the file path in configuration.

After fix:
- Script successfully detected PID
- Alert stopped triggering

## 📚 Key Learning
Monitoring failures are not always system failures.

Small configuration issues can lead to false alerts and unnecessary noise.

